  "A population of bacteria grows at a rate proportional to its size, described by dP/dt = 0.5P. If there are 100 bacteria initially, how many are there after 4 hours?": "",
  "100e^2 bacteria": "",
  "400 bacteria": "",
  "200 bacteria": "",
  "100e^4 bacteria": "",
  "The general solution of dP/dt = 0.5P is P = P_0 * e^(0.5t). With P_0 = 100: P(4) = 100e^(0.5*4) = 100e^2 bacteria (approximately 739).": "",
  "A cup of coffee cools according to dT/dt = -0.1(T - 70), where T is temperature in degrees F and 70 is room temperature. If T(0) = 200, write the particular solution.": "",
  "T(t) = 70 + 200e^(-0.1t)": "",
  "T(t) = 70 + 130e^(-0.1t)": "",
  "T(t) = 200e^(-0.1t)": "",
  "T(t) = 130e^(-0.1t)": "",
  "This is Newton's Law of Cooling. Let u = T - 70, so du/dt = -0.1u, giving u = Ce^(-0.1t). Since T(0) = 200, u(0) = 130, so C = 130. Therefore T = 70 + 130e^(-0.1t).": "",
  "A tank initially contains 50 gallons of pure water. Saltwater with concentration 2 lb/gal flows in at 3 gal/min, and the well-mixed solution flows out at 3 gal/min. Write the differential equation for the amount of salt A(t).": "",
  "dA/dt = 6 - 3A/50": "",
  "dA/dt = 6 - A": "",
  "dA/dt = 3 - 2A/50": "",
  "dA/dt = 2 - 3A": "",
  "Salt comes in at rate 2 lb/gal * 3 gal/min = 6 lb/min. Salt goes out at concentration A/50 lb/gal times 3 gal/min = 3A/50 lb/min. Therefore dA/dt = 6 - 3A/50.": "",
  "A savings account earns continuous interest at 5% per year. If you continuously withdraw $1000 per year, the balance B satisfies dB/dt = 0.05B - 1000. If B(0) = $30,000, what is the equilibrium balance?": "",
